I define automation strategy by first studying the current system landscape and delivery pipeline.
Step 1: Assess Current State
How many apps?
What type: monolith, microservices?
What tests exist?
Where is CI/CD slow?
Where are defects coming from?

Step 2: Define Test Distribution  I strictly follow:
API & Integration tests for most coverage
UI only for critical journeys
Avoid UI-heavy regression

Step 3: Platform Strategy Build or standardize:
One UI framework     One API framework          Shared utilities

Make framework:
           Easy to use
           Pipeline-friendly
           Config-driven
           Parallel execution ready

Step 4: CI/CD Integration
           PR ‚Üí Smoke tests
           Merge ‚Üí API + Integration
           Nightly ‚Üí Full regression
Auto reports + quality gates

Step 5: Stability & Scale
           Flaky test dashboard
           Retry only at framework level
           Test data auto-generation
           Mocking downstream services

Step 6: Team Adoption Create:
Starter templates
Documentation

ExamplesDo:
Code reviews  Training sessions   Best practice sharing
üéØ Closing Line
So my strategy is to build a scalable automation ecosystem, not just a test suite.
